### Local Development

```bash
# Clone repository
git clone https://github.com/MUNQU/commol.git
cd commol

# Create and activate virtual environment
python -m venv venv

source venv/bin/activate  # On Linux/macOS
venv\Scripts\activate   # On Windows

# Install Python dependencies
cd py-commol
pip install -e ".[dev,docs]"

# Build Rust workspace
cd ..
cargo build --workspace

# Build Python extension (with virtual environment activated)
cd py-commol
maturin develop --release

# Run tests
pytest
cd ..
cargo test --workspace

# Build documentation locally
cd py-commol
mkdocs serve
```

> **‚ö†Ô∏è Path Requirements**: Ensure the project path contains no tildes (`~`) or spaces. Maturin may fail otherwise.
>
> **üí° Tip**: Make sure your virtual environment is activated before running `maturin develop`.

